    </teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter">
                    <ab><title>Genesis <supplied reason="lost">20</supplied></title>
                        <milestone unit="line" xml:id="line-8-2" n="8" prev="ADub.III.73.001.019.trl.xml#line-8-1"/>
                        <l n="1">And Abraham journeyed from there toward the land
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                            of the south and dwelt between Kadesh
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                            and Shur and lived in Gerar.</l>
                        <l n="2">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                            Abraham said of Sarah his wife, ‘She is my sister.’ And Abimelech,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                            king of Gerar, sent and took Sarah.</l>
                        <l n="3">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                            an angel came to Abimelech through a dream of the night, and said
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                            to him, ‘Lo, you will die because of that woman that you have taken, for
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                            she is wedded to a man.’</l>
                        <l n="4">But Abimelech had not approached
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                            her, and he said, ‘Oh Lord, will you kill a righteous kingdom as
                            well?</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                        <l n="5">Lo, that man said to me, “She is my sister.”
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                            And the woman — she, too — said, “He is my brother.” I did this in the integrity
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                            of my heart and in the cleanness of my palms.’</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                        <l n="6">And God said to him through the dream, ‘I know, too,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                            that you did this in the integrity of your heart. Because of that
                            <milestone unit="page" n="28r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                            I have kept you, too, from being sinful against me. Therefore
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                            I did not let you touch her.</l>
                        <l n="7">Now, return
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                            the man’s wife, because he is a prophet, and he shall pray for you,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                            and you will live. But if you do not return her, know that you will
                            surely die,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                            you and all who are yours.’</l>
                        <l n="8">So
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                            Abimelech rose up early at dawn and called all his servants
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                            and told them all these things in their ears.
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                            And the men were very much afraid.</l>
                        <l n="9">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                            And Abimelech called Abraham, and said to him, ‘What have you done
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                            to us? And how did I sin against you, that you have almost brought a
                            great sin on
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                            me and on my kingdom? You have done things
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                            with me that are not done.’</l>
                        <l n="10">And Abimelech said
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                            to Abraham, ‘What did you see, that you did this thing?’</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                        <l n="11">And Abraham said, ‘Because I said, “Yet there is no
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                            fear of God at all in this place, and they will kill me
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                            because of my wife.”</l>
                        <l n="11">And also she is, indeed, my sister,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                            she is the daughter of my father, but not the daughter of my mother, and
                            she became
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                            a wife to me.</l>
                        <l n="13">And it was, when God ordered
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                            me to go from my father’s house, that I said to her,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                            “This shall be the kindness which you shall do with me: to every place where
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                            we come, say about me, “He is my brother.””’</l>
                        <milestone unit="page" n="28v" />
                        <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                        <l n="14">And Abimelech took sheep, and cattle, and servants, and
                            maidservants, and gave them to Abraham,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                            and returned Sarah, his wife, to him.</l>
                        <l n="15">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                            Abimelech said to Abraham, ‘Lo, my land is before you.
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                            Dwell at the place that would seem good in your eyes.’</l>
                        <l n="16">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                            And to Sarah he said, ‘Lo, I have given your brother a thousand pieces
                            of silver.
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                            Lo, it is a covering of eyes for you, for all that are with you.’
                                <delSpan spanTo="#del001" />seg type="commented" n="#seg007"/<anchor
                                xml:id="del001" />And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                            after hearing all of this, Sarah was reproved for saying
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                            about her husband, ‘He is my brother.’<delSpan spanTo="#del002" />anchor
                            type="commented" xml:id="seg007"/<anchor xml:id="del002" /><ref
                                target="#fn1" type="noteAnchor" /></l>
                        <l n="17">So
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                            Abraham prayed to God, and God healed
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                            Abimelech, and his wife and his maidservants, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                            they bore.</l>
                        <l n="18">Because the Lord had surely closed every
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                            womb of the house of Abimelech, because of Sarah,
                            <milestone unit="line" xml:id="line-13-1" n="13" next="ADub.III.73.001.021.trl.xml#line-13-2"/>
                            Abraham’s wife.</l>
                    </ab>
                </div>
